Fill and boil your #kettle{}.

Fill a large #saucepan{} with the boiled water from your kettle and put on high
heat.

Add @salt{1/2%tsp} and the @linguine{180%g}. Bring back to the boil.

Cook until tender, ~{12%mins}.

While the pasta cooks, heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on high
heat.

Once hot, add the @sliced mushrooms{80%g} and @British smoked bacon lardons{60%g}.

Cook, stirring occasionally, until golden all over, ~{4-5%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon
> thoroughly.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Trim the bottom 2cm from the @asparagus{100%g} and discard. Halve the asparagus
widthways.

Once the mushrooms and bacon are golden, stir in the garlic and cook for
~{30%secs}.

When the pasta has 3 mins left, add the asparagus to the same frying pan and
cook for the remaining time.

Once the pasta and asparagus are cooked, reserve some of the pasta water (see
pantry for amount), then drain in a #colander{}. Drizzle with oil and stir
through to prevent it sticking.

Stir the @reserved pasta water{100%ml}, @creme fraiche{150%g} and
@chicken stock paste{10%g} into the mushrooms and bacon.

Add the cooked pasta, asparagus and @hard Italian style cheese{40%g}(grated)
to the sauce and gently toss to coat.

Add another splash of water if the sauce is a bit thick. Season to taste with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

Share the bacon and mushroom linguine between your bowls.

Enjoy!